        <p>
            We have been evaluating expressions, but we can evaluate formulas in the same way.
            A <term>formula</term>                                                                                      <idx><h>formula</h></idx>
            has a single variable that represents the result of an expression,
            then an equals sign, then an expression on the right of the equals sign.
            For example, a formula for a person's maximum heart rate in beats per minute is <m>H=220-a</m>,
            where <m>a</m> is their age.
        </p>
