        <page>
            <exercise>
                <introduction>
                    <p>
                        Let <m>a</m> be a person's age (in years)
                        and let <m>H</m> be a person's target heart rate (in beats per minute).
                        If a person wants to improve their overall health,
                        then the lower limit of their target heart rate is given by
                        <me>H=0.5(220-a)</me>
                        The upper limit of their target heart rate is given by
                        <me>H=0.6(220-a)</me>
                    </p>
                </introduction>
                <task workspace="3.5in">
                    <p>
                        Determine the lower limit for the target heart rate of someone who is <m>20</m> years old.
                    </p>
                </task>
                <task workspace="3.5in">
                    <p>
                        Determine the upper limit for the target heart rate of someone who is <m>70</m> years old.
                    </p>
                </task>
